    },
    "content" : "Getting stuck in there Steve, nice one \n<img src=\"./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\" alt=\":wink:\" title=\"Wink\"> \n<br>\n<br>The 59 would have had thick lip dog legs (mine's late December '59 and has factory thick lips)\n<br>\n<br>In fact my 62 crossover split had thick lips too, so yours is squarely in the right range for these.\n<br>\n<br>Hope this helps mate.\n<br>\n<br>Cheers.\n<br>\n<br>Nik \n<img src=\"./images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif\" alt=\":D\" title=\"Big Grin\">",
    "lastEdited" : "Thu Oct 30, 2014 7:55 pm"
  }, {
    "postId" : "808623",
    "author" : {
      "username" : "clymoj",
      "userId" : "Unknown",
      "joined" : "-",
      "profileRank" : "-",
      "location" : "-",
      "postCount" : "-",
      "avatarPath" : "http://i1068.photobucket.com/albums/u451/clymoj/Bus/Bus005_zps44edd617.jpg"
    },
    "content" : "Scary seeing it all stripped back isn't it and you'll have few big gulps before the cutting's finished but will be worth it to know it's done right.\n<br>\n<br>Thick lip for &lt;62 yes, thin lip 63&lt;. Thick lip only started being available fairly recently so older work will have incorrectly used thin lip regardless. I had the same on my bus (but on both sides).\n<br>\n<br>I was told use Autocraft for everything they make, so bought everything from there and have been very pleased. Excellent service and the panels fit!\n<br>\n<br>I've also heard from good body shops that Schofields are good and stock the best available panel by panel whether that be autocraft or others; but I don't have first hand experience. They have an excellent reputation for general parts, advice and service which I can confirm.",
    "lastEdited" : "Thu Oct 30, 2014 8:59 pm"
  }, {
    "postId" : "808713",
    "author" : {
